Reasoning: The paper discusses the ability of decision makers to form abstractions and the use of information theory in decision making. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to artificial intelligence, machine learning, information theory, and systems. Specifically, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely categories given the focus on decision making and abstraction. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely given the use of information theoretic concepts. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible categories given the potential application of the ideas presented in the paper to these fields.
